summary: I think i said before how one of the core themes shared by Good Omens and the Death Gate Cycle series is how You Need Two To...
body:
I think i said before how one of the core themes shared by Good Omens and the Death Gate Cycle series is how You Need Two To Tango- both sides want the war and neither care much about human lives, no matter how much they try to present themselves as the perfect good side. in reality, it turns out that both of the sides are corrupt at best and the humans having authority over themselves and free will is the best solution.

today I realized another thing shared is how arbitrary the sides are. all the demons were angels, and though the fall changed them and the way of operation, it was a political schism- jsut like we discover that the Patryn and the Sartan are actually one species (which is still genetically compatible, for crying out loud) and the whole divide thing is cultural at best, almost national- even the magic systems seen as opposite were actually halves of a whole.

just like the demons, the only core difference between Patryn and Sartan is who walked out and reclaimed the darkness in those ancient times and who stayed, and like heaven the Sartan kept labeling themselves bringers of light while coldly pursuing a plan that would destroy the world (both cases against god’s hidden will, if Crowley and Aziraphale’s ideas about a second hidden plan are right).

summary:
Reporter Rose Tyler follows a rather irritating lead.
"You've been following me again."
"Well, you've left a trail from London...
body:
Reporter Rose Tyler follows a rather irritating lead.

“You’ve been following me again.”

“Well, you’ve left a trail from London to Oxfordshire and back again. You’re not exactly subtle.”

“I was preventing the apocalypse, Rose! There was hardly time for subtlety.”

“And last night?”

“The cabbie was irritating me.”

“Demons are so predictable. C'mon, Crowley, with me. This cover-up isn’t going to write itself.”

“Can I take my ice lolly?”

“Only if you go back and pay for it.”

“It represents,” said Crowley, “Good and Evil wrestling with Evil triumphing.”
Aziraphale’s eyes narrowed. “Are you certain that they’re wrestling?” he asked.

So… it was confirmed that The Statue™ is going to be included in the series adaption.
